<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-14T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/628: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Earle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-14T16:00:00+02:00">January
                                    14, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. The German-controlled newspapers here four times in the last week
                            were about to publish vicious articles against President Roosevelt. The
                            Foreign Minister<note n="21" xml:id="d290fn21">Ivan Popov.</note>
                            personally had every word of them barred from publication. Only one
                            anti-American article in a small weekly escaped him.</p>
                        <p>The censorship is under the Minister of the Interior, Gabrovsky, who is
                            pro-German. There is a struggle going on between him and the Foreign
                            Minister with the outcome uncertain.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>